  "prompt": "What are some must see places in coorg?",
  "response": "Coorg (Kodagu) is a beautiful district in Karnataka known for its scenic landscapes, coffee plantations, and rich culture. Here are some must-see places:\n\n1. Natural Attractions\n- Abbey Falls\n- Mallalli Falls\n- Raja's Seat\n- Mandalpatti View Point\n- Talacauvery (Origin of River Cauvery)\n\n2. Historical & Cultural Sites\n- Madikeri Fort\n- Omkareshwara Temple\n- Bylakuppe Golden Temple (Tibetan Monastery)\n\n3. Wildlife & National Parks\n- Nagarhole National Park\n- Pushpagiri Wildlife Sanctuary\n\n4. Coffee Plantations\n- Take a guided tour of coffee estates\n- Learn about coffee processing\n- Enjoy plantation walks\n\n5. Adventure Destinations\n- Brahmagiri Hill Trek\n- Dubare Elephant Camp\n- Rafting in River Cauvery\n\n6. Other Attractions\n- Chettalli Village\n- Bagamandala\n- Nisargadhama Forest Resort\n\n7. Cultural Experiences\n- Explore local Kodava cuisine\n- Visit local markets\n- Attend traditional festivals\n\nThese places offer a mix of natural beauty, cultural experiences, and adventure activities.",
